  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Border Management to Mitigate the Risk of Terrorism from Land and Maritime Borders in the Context of COVID-19</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the proposed intervention is to enhance border security and national stability in light of the COVID19 context, through an improved response and strengthened coordination among border management agencies to effectively combat terrorism threats and other transnational organized crime. OM aims to support the Government of Uganda, through close coordination with the border management agencies of Immigration, Security, Customs and Health to inter-alia, improve preparedness and identification of terrorist groups through points of entry and develop capacities against terrorist attempts to launder money. IOM Uganda has previously engaged in several initiatives such as joint training activities, provision of border management equipment such as vehicles and ICT support. However, with the effects of COVID-19 and a shift in priorities to health, states require now, more than before, an increase of border security efforts through a dedicated border management project aimed at counterterrorism.</narrative>
  </description>
